From: Christophe Leroy <christophe.leroy@csgroup.eu>
Date: Tue, 8 Dec 2020 05:24:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] powerpc/powermac: Fix low_sleep_handler with
 CONFIG_VMAP_STACK
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.10.4
Git-commit: db972a3787d12b1ce9ba7a31ec376d8a79e04c47

[ Upstream commit db972a3787d12b1ce9ba7a31ec376d8a79e04c47 ]

low_sleep_handler() can't restore the context from standard
stack because the stack can hardly be accessed with MMU OFF.

Store everything in a global storage area instead of storing
a pointer to the stack in that global storage area.

To avoid a complete churn of the function, still use r1 as
the pointer to the storage area during restore.

Fixes: cd08f109e262 ("powerpc/32s: Enable CONFIG_VMAP_STACK")
